Podcast Description In this episode, we are once again joined by Josh Graham from Roost Mortgages. And we discuss whether you can get an interest-only loan forever.
The general rule of thumb is that an interest-only loan period will run for 5 years. At the end of those 5-years you can apply for another 5-year period.&nbsp;
However, the bank will always consider whether you can afford the higher principal and interest payments once the interest-only period has finished.

